'''The Center for Reliability Research''' (CRR) is a research center at the aerospace research institute, [[Tehran]], Iran, Established in 2009, the center includes Institute faculty and staff and external associates. It is involved in research in [[Reliability engineering]], modeling and assessment. the first Iranian reliability software has been developed by this center. this center organized and held three conference on reliability engineering(Oct.2009,Oct. 2011,<ref>{{cite web|title=Conference|url=http://reli2011.ari.ac.ir/English.htm|publisher=Aerospace research Inst.|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20151014173007/http%3A//reli2011.ari.ac.ir/English.htm|archivedate=2015-10-14|df=}}</ref> Feb. 2014).
