{{Infobox organization |image= |name=Coalition to Diversify Computing |founded_date= |location= |origins= |key_people= |area_served=International |focus=Diversity in Computing |revenue= |endowment= |owner= |Non-profit_slogan= |former name= |homepage={{URL|http://www.cdc-computing.org/}} }} The '''Coalition to Diversify Computing (CDC)''' is a joint organization of the [[Association for Computing Machinery]] (ACM) and the [[Computing Research Association]] (CRA).<ref name=website>[http://www.cdc-computing.org/ CDC home]</ref> CDC emphasizes recruiting minority undergraduates to MS/PhD programs, retaining minority graduate students enrolled in MS/PhD programs, and transitioning minority MS/PhD graduates into academia, industry, and government careers.<ref name=website />
